e- and English-language sources, Exporting Virtue? investigates the challenges that China’s human rights orthodoxy poses to international norms and institutions, offering normative and institutional analysis and providing suggestions for policy response.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aCommunismzChina. 0aHuman rights advocacyzChinaxHistoryy21st century. 0aHuman rights movementszChinaxHistoryy21st century. 0aHuman rightszChinaxHistoryy21st century. 70(DE-588)4038463-90(DE-627)1047747110(DE-576)209030216aMeinungsfreiheit2gnd 70(DE-588)4074725-60(DE-627)1060885560(DE-576)209195088aMenschenrecht2gnd 70(DE-588)4113450-30(DE-627)1058293900(DE-576)209476583aEntwicklung2gnd 70(DE-588)4127674-70(DE-627)1057230370(DE-576)209595566aInformationsfreiheit2gnd 70(DE-588)4169433-80(DE-627)1054100470(DE-576)20992277XaMenschenrechtspolitik2gnd 70(DE-588)4180271-80(DE-627)1041222770(DE-576)209996986aSchutz2gnd 70(DE-588)4253944-40(DE-627)1043531040(DE-576)210535237aInternationale Norm2gnd 70(DE-588)4276272-80(DE-627)1044234200(DE-576)210723971aMenschenrechtsverletzung2gnd 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / Human Rights.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Complete eBook-Package 2021z978311127221408iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Upgrade eBook-Package 2021z978311127464508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of British Columbia Complete eBook-Package 2021z978311141764640uhttps://doi.org/10.59962/978077486557940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780774865579423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780774865579/original  a978-3-11-127221-4  ACUP Complete eBook-Package 2021b2021  a978-3-11-127464-5  ACUP Upgrade eBook-Package 2021b2021  a978-3-11-141764-6  University of British Columbia Compl